# Apurv Branch: Firebase → Supabase Optimization Notes

This document summarizes the key optimizations done in this branch so anyone can quickly understand what changed and why.

## 1) Migration Focus: Firebase to Supabase

- Migrated core data access flows to Supabase-backed tables and services.
- Standardized reads through Supabase query patterns used across pages/services.
- Added and maintained Supabase migration files under:
  - `supabase/migrations/`
  - `supabase/uat_export/production_public_schema.sql`

## 2) Reduced Redundant Code

- Consolidated repeated profile-table column selections into one shared constant file:
  - `lib/constants/profile_table_columns.dart`
- Added `columnsForProfileTable(...)` so the same profile projection logic is reused instead of duplicated in many pages.
- This reduces repeated query definitions and keeps profile fetch logic consistent.

## 3) Stopped Fetching Entire Tables Where Not Needed

- Replaced broad/full-row fetch patterns in many profile-related reads with explicit column projections.
- Client/artist/brand screens now use targeted `select(...)` columns instead of unnecessarily loading all fields in common paths.
- Example usage appears across:
  - `lib/pages/client_*`
  - `lib/pages/brand_*`
  - `lib/pages/client_artists_page.dart`
  - `lib/pages/client_home_page.dart`
  - `lib/pages/client_profile_page.dart`

## 4) Indexing and Query Performance Improvements

Indexes are present to support faster lookups and filtering on important workloads.

### Client-related request flows

- `client_custom_requests` indexes include:
  - client email/id/uid
  - selected/accepted artist email
  - status, artist_status, client_status
  - created_at, updated_at, need_by, order_number

### Artist-related flows

- Artist-centric lookups are optimized with indexes such as:
  - `reviews_artist_id_idx`
  - `tip_payout_queue_artist_email_idx`
  - `tips_artist_id_idx`
  - `idx_ascension_audit_logs_artist_id`

### Brand/company flows

- `company_custom_requests` includes indexes for:
  - company/client/artist email filters
  - selected/accepted artist or client email
  - status and lifecycle fields
  - created_at, need_by, order_number

### Source of index definitions

- See `supabase/uat_export/production_public_schema.sql` (`CREATE INDEX` statements).

## 5) Outcome

- Less redundant query code.
- Reduced over-fetching in important UI flows.
- Better read/query performance through indexed access patterns.
- Clearer separation of data-access concerns while moving from Firebase-style patterns to Supabase-native structures.
